  "text": "# Prometheus Metric Registration Patterns Across Projects\n\n## Overview\nThe three repositories implement distinct but related patterns for Prometheus metric registration and exposure. Each approach reflects different design philosophies:\n\n## 1. Kubernetes (kubernetes/kubernetes)\n**Pattern: Stability-Aware Custom Registry Wrapper**\n\nKubernetes implements the most sophisticated pattern using a custom `KubeRegistry` interface that wraps `prometheus.Registry`. This approach prioritizes metric stability and deprecation management.\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/registry.go`: Core `KubeRegistry` interface implementing custom `Register()` and `MustRegister()` methods that handle metric stability levels (ALPHA, BETA, STABLE). The registry tracks deprecated metrics and hidden collectors based on Kubernetes version.\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/counter.go`, `histogram.go`, `gauge.go`: Custom metric wrappers around prometheus metrics. These implement lazy initialization and use Kubernetes-specific options like `StabilityLevel` and `DeprecatedVersion`.\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/legacyregistry/registry.go`: Provides global registry functions (`MustRegister`, `Register`, `Registerer`) that delegate to a singleton `kubeRegistry` instance. This file also initializes default collectors (Process and Go runtime metrics) and calls `RegisterMetaMetrics()`.\n\n**Registration Mechanism:**\n```\nNewKubeRegistry() -> kubeRegistry (wraps prometheus.NewRegistry())\n  -> Register(Registerable) / MustRegister(...Registerable)\n    -> Checks stability level and deprecation status via Create(version)\n    -> Delegates to underlying prometheus.Registry.Register()\n    -> Tracks hidden and resettable collectors\n```\n\n## 2. Prometheus (prometheus/prometheus)\n**Pattern: Direct Interface Usage with Component-Level Metrics**\n\nPrometheus uses the native Prometheus client library interfaces (`prometheus.Registerer`, `prometheus.Gatherer`) directly. Metrics are organized by component/discovery mechanism.\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `discovery/metrics.go`: Generic `NewManagerMetrics()` function that creates and registers discovery manager metrics (FailedConfigs, DiscoveredTargets, ReceivedUpdates). Returns metrics struct with unregister capability.\n- `scrape/metrics.go`: `newScrapeMetrics()` creates comprehensive scrape pool metrics including SummaryVecs, HistogramVecs, and Counters. All metrics are registered in a loop via `reg.Register()` with error handling.\n- `discovery/azure/metrics.go`, `discovery/consul/metrics.go`, etc.: Each discovery backend has a `newDiscovererMetrics()` function that creates backend-specific metrics and registers them through `discovery.NewMetricRegisterer()`.\n- `cmd/prometheus/main.go`: Uses `prometheus.MustRegister()` directly for version collector and custom metrics.\n\n**Registration Mechanism:**\n```\nfunction newScrapeMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer) {\n  sm := &scrapeMetrics{reg: reg}\n  // Create metrics via prometheus.NewCounter(), prometheus.NewGauge(), etc.\n  // Register in loop: for _, collector := range collectors { reg.Register(collector) }\n  return sm\n}\n```\n\n## 3. Grafana (grafana/grafana)\n**Pattern: Global Metric Variables with Centralized Registration**\n\nGrafana defines metrics as global variables initialized in `init()` functions, then registers them centrally through a metrics service. This allows flexible registerer injection and custom gathering logic.\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `pkg/infra/metrics/metrics.go`: Defines all global metric variables (MInstanceStart, MPageStatus, MApiStatus, etc.) as prometheus types, creates them via `prometheus.NewCounter()`, `prometheus.NewGauge()`, `prometheus.NewSummary()` in `init()`. The `initMetricVars(reg)` function batches registration via `reg.MustRegister()`.\n- `pkg/infra/metrics/service.go`: `ProvideService()` calls `initMetricVars(reg)` and `initFrontendMetrics(reg)`. `ProvideRegisterer()` uses `legacyregistry.Registerer()` (Kubernetes' global registry). `ProvideGatherer()` wraps gatherers with `addPrefixWrapper` and `multiRegistry` for prefix injection and deduplication.\n- `apps/plugins/pkg/app/metrics/metrics.go`: Shows module-specific pattern with global metric variables and `MustRegister()` function that registers all metrics in a loop.\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/metrics.go`: Module metrics defined in `init()`, with separate `RegisterMetrics(reg)` function for explicit registration.\n- `pkg/registry/apis/iam/metrics.go`, `provisioning/controller/metrics.go`: Use `sync.Once` with `registerOnce.Do()` to ensure single registration, demonstrating deduplication pattern.\n\n**Registration Mechanism:**\n```\nvar MInstanceStart prometheus.Counter\n\nfunc init() {\n  MInstanceStart = prometheus.NewCounter(...)\n}\n\nfunc initMetricVars(reg prometheus.Registerer) {\n  reg.MustRegister(MInstanceStart, MPageStatus, ...)\n}\n```\n\n## Key Differences\n\n| Aspect | Kubernetes | Prometheus | Grafana |\n|--------|-----------|-----------|----------|\n| **Registry Type** | Custom KubeRegistry wrapper | Native prometheus.Registry | prometheus.Registry via interface |\n| **Metric Definition** | Wrapped types (Counter, Histogram, Gauge) | Native prometheus types | Native prometheus types |\n| **Registration** | Via KubeRegistry.Register() with stability checks | Direct prometheus.Registerer.Register() | Via initMetricVars() batch registration |\n| **Stability Management** | Built-in deprecation lifecycle | None | None |\n| **Error Handling** | Tracked and counted | Return error or panic in registration loop | MustRegister panics on error |\n| **Organization** | Centralized wrapper classes | Component-specific metrics.go files | Module-specific metrics.go + centralized service |\n| **Initialization** | NewKubeRegistry() + global legacyregistry | Component-level new*Metrics() functions | Global init() + service injection |\n\n## Registration Flow Summary\n\n**Kubernetes Flow:**\n```\nlegacyregistry.MustRegister() \n  -> kubeRegistry.MustRegister(Registerable...) \n    -> Registerable.Create(version) \n    -> prometheus.Registry.MustRegister(prometheus.Collector...)\n```\n\n**Prometheus Flow:**\n```\nnew*Metrics(prometheus.Registerer) \n  -> prometheus.NewCounter/Gauge/Histogram() \n  -> registerer.Register(collector) [with error handling]\n```\n\n**Grafana Flow:**\n```\ninit() { global metric vars = prometheus.New*() }\nProvideService(registerer, gatherer) \n  -> initMetricVars(registerer) \n    -> registerer.MustRegister(metric1, metric2, ...)\n```"
}
